262
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:35,480
Now, let's start with an important idea.

263
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:42,660
The fallacy of a single number in software engineering.

264
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:52,970
Very often in software projects, we try to reduce complex concepts.

265
00:32:52,970 --> 00:33:07,289
Like quality, complexity, or effort into just one number.

266
00:33:07,289 --> 00:33:12,640
We feel comfortable when we see a single value.

267
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:18,119
It looks clear, objective, and easy to compare.

268
00:33:18,119 --> 00:33:21,119
But this can be misleading.

