00:53:14,760 --> 00:53:16,760
The verdict is important.

557
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:24,760
Forcing different code structures into a single order of scale creates a false hierarchy.

558
00:53:24,760 --> 00:53:30,889
It gives us clarity, but possibly at the cost of truth.

559
00:53:30,889 --> 00:53:46,239
The real question is, are we measuring complexity or are we only measuring one aspect of it and pretending it presents the whole?

560
00:53:46,239 --> 00:54:02,159
So, if a single real number does not work, what is the solution?

561
00:54:02,159 --> 00:54:10,099
The answer is vector representation.

562
00:54:10,099 --> 00:54:21,389
Instead of mapping entities into the set of real numbers R, we map them into R by R.

563
00:54:21,389 --> 00:54:23,389
Or more generally into an array of numbers.

564
00:54:23,389 --> 00:54:24,389
And this is the solution.

565
00:54:24,389 --> 00:54:34,900
This means we represent each entity using multiple values, not just one.

566
00:54:34,900 --> 00:54:43,900
In the transport example, we defined m transport equals time and cost.

567
00:54:43,900 --> 00:54:52,900
So, instead of seeing car has quality 7.2,

