00:55:15,250 --> 00:55:17,250
Now we preserve both dimensions.

571
00:55:17,250 --> 00:55:22,250
In this case, we do not lose both information.

572
00:55:22,250 --> 00:55:29,250
And most importantly, we preserve the empirical relationships.

573
00:55:29,250 --> 00:55:33,280
If one option is better in both time and cost,

574
00:55:33,280 --> 00:55:41,280
then superiority is visible in the pair comparison.

575
00:55:41,280 --> 00:55:45,699
This is the key idea.

576
00:55:45,699 --> 00:55:54,760
When data is multidimensional, the representation must also be multidimensional.

577
00:55:54,760 --> 00:55:58,760
And this is not just a theoretical idea.

578
00:55:58,760 --> 00:56:04,360
It is exactly the approach taken by idealists.

579
00:56:04,360 --> 00:56:12,360
The approach taken by ISO IEC 25010 for software quality.

580
00:56:12,360 --> 00:56:19,369
This standard does not define quality as a single number.

581
00:56:19,369 --> 00:56:27,369
Instead, it defines software quality as a set of distinct sub-attributes,

582
00:56:27,369 --> 00:56:35,659
such as functional suitability, performance comparability,

583
00:56:36,980 --> 00:56:43,980
usability, reliability, security, maintainability, and portability.

584
00:56:43,980 --> 00:56:52,559
In other words, software quality is treated as a vector,

585
00:56:52,559 --> 00:56:56,559
a structured set of attributes.

586
00:56:56,559 --> 00:57:04,250
We must stop flattening multidimensional data into a single scalar value.

587
00:57:04,250 --> 00:57:08,250
When we do that, we are simply too much.

588
00:57:08,250 --> 00:57:11,250
And risk misrepresentation.

589
00:57:11,250 --> 00:57:20,389
So, instead of asking what is the quality number,

590
00:57:20,389 --> 00:57:29,610
a better question is what are the relevant dimensions and how do they interact?

591
00:57:29,610 --> 00:57:42,150
The rules of derivative measurements.

592
00:57:42,150 --> 00:57:49,360
Now, let's talk about the rules of derivative measurements.

