817
01:11:13,789 --> 01:11:14,789
A model,

818
01:11:14,789 --> 01:11:15,789
yes,

819
01:11:15,789 --> 01:11:18,789
may be mathematically meaningful,

820
01:11:18,789 --> 01:11:21,789
but still inaccurate.

821
01:11:21,789 --> 01:11:25,090
So,

822
01:11:25,090 --> 01:11:28,279
the real conclusion is

823
01:11:28,279 --> 01:11:31,279
Watson-Felix model is meaningful

824
01:11:31,279 --> 01:11:33,279
in the wide sense

825
01:11:33,279 --> 01:11:37,279
because it preserves ratio scale properties.

826
01:11:37,279 --> 01:11:39,279
The mathematics is consistent

827
01:11:39,279 --> 01:11:41,279
with measurement theory,

828
01:11:41,279 --> 01:11:44,279
but whether the model predicts

829
01:11:44,279 --> 01:11:47,279
effort accurately in practice

830
01:11:47,279 --> 01:11:52,319
is a separate empirical question.

831
01:11:52,319 --> 01:11:59,840
This case study teaches us something powerful.

832
01:11:59,840 --> 01:12:03,199
Before rejecting a model,

833
01:12:03,199 --> 01:12:05,199
we must check whether

834
01:12:05,199 --> 01:12:09,199
the criticism is about scale theory

835
01:12:09,199 --> 01:12:13,199
or about empirical validity.

836
01:12:13,199 --> 01:12:18,359
These are two different issues.

837
01:12:18,359 --> 01:12:26,399
Yes,

838
01:12:26,399 --> 01:12:28,399
the trap of mixed scales

839
01:12:28,399 --> 01:12:32,739
halstits physics.

840
01:12:32,739 --> 01:12:34,739
Now,

841
01:12:34,739 --> 01:12:36,800
let's look

842
01:12:36,800 --> 01:12:38,800
at a very important warning.

843
01:12:38,800 --> 01:12:42,989
The trap of mixed scales

844
01:12:42,989 --> 01:12:45,949
illustrated by

845
01:12:45,949 --> 01:12:47,949
Halstits physics.

846
01:12:47,949 --> 01:12:51,239
Halstits proposed a theory

847
01:12:51,239 --> 01:12:55,239
where software effort is defined as

848
01:12:55,239 --> 01:12:58,239
E is equal to

849
01:12:58,239 --> 01:13:00,239
V over L.

850
01:13:00,239 --> 01:13:03,090
Here,

851
01:13:03,090 --> 01:13:07,239
V is program volume

852
01:13:07,239 --> 01:13:11,010
and is program level.

853
01:13:11,010 --> 01:13:14,010
According to Halstits,

854
01:13:14,010 --> 01:13:16,010
this equation measures

855
01:13:16,010 --> 01:13:19,010
the mental efforts required

856
01:13:19,010 --> 01:13:21,970
to implement a program.

857
01:13:21,970 --> 01:13:23,970
At first glance,

858
01:13:23,970 --> 01:13:26,970
it looks similar to the density example

859
01:13:26,970 --> 01:13:29,000
we saw before.

860
01:13:29,000 --> 01:13:31,000
It's a simple division.

861
01:13:31,000 --> 01:13:33,000
It feels mathematically clean.

862
01:13:33,000 --> 01:13:35,000
But now,

863
01:13:35,000 --> 01:13:40,189
we must examine the scale types carefully.

864
01:13:40,189 --> 01:13:42,189
Volume V is measured

865
01:13:42,189 --> 01:13:44,189
on a ratio scale,

866
01:13:44,189 --> 01:13:46,409
but

867
01:13:46,409 --> 01:13:48,409
it's based on

868
01:13:48,409 --> 01:13:51,409
counts of operators

869
01:13:51,409 --> 01:13:54,180
and operands.

870
01:13:54,180 --> 01:13:57,180
It has a true zero

871
01:13:57,180 --> 01:14:00,180
and allows proportional comparisons.

872
01:14:00,180 --> 01:14:02,630
Program level L, however,

873
01:14:02,630 --> 01:14:06,630
is only on an ordinal scale,

874
01:14:06,630 --> 01:14:09,720
which represents a ranking

875
01:14:09,720 --> 01:14:12,720
or an estimated level,

876
01:14:12,720 --> 01:14:14,720
not a true ratio measure.

877
01:14:14,720 --> 01:14:17,300
And here is the

878
01:14:17,300 --> 01:14:20,300
fatal flaw.

879
01:14:20,300 --> 01:14:22,720
According

880
01:14:22,720 --> 01:14:24,720
to the weakest link rule,

881
01:14:24,720 --> 01:14:26,720
a derivative measure

882
01:14:26,720 --> 01:14:28,720
cannot be stronger than

883
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:30,720
its weakest components.

884
01:14:30,720 --> 01:14:33,720
Since L is ordinal,

885
01:14:33,720 --> 01:14:34,720
the result E

886
01:14:34,720 --> 01:14:36,720
cannot be ratio scale.

887
01:14:36,720 --> 01:14:40,680
But Halstits claims

888
01:14:40,680 --> 01:14:42,680
that

889
01:14:42,680 --> 01:14:44,680
E measures

890
01:14:44,680 --> 01:14:46,710
mental

891
01:14:46,710 --> 01:14:48,710
discriminations

892
01:14:48,710 --> 01:14:49,710
which would require

893
01:14:49,710 --> 01:14:51,710
a ratio scale.

894
01:14:51,710 --> 01:14:52,739
That would mean

895
01:14:52,739 --> 01:14:54,739
we could

896
01:14:54,739 --> 01:14:55,739
meaningfully say

897
01:14:55,739 --> 01:14:58,739
one program requires twice

898
01:14:58,739 --> 01:15:00,739
as much mental effort

899
01:15:00,739 --> 01:15:02,739
as another.

900
01:15:02,739 --> 01:15:07,180
This is mathematically impossible.

901
01:15:07,180 --> 01:15:08,180
You cannot derive

902
01:15:08,180 --> 01:15:10,180
a ratio scale measure

903
01:15:10,180 --> 01:15:13,180
from an ordinal input.

904
01:15:13,180 --> 01:15:17,180
The scale type collapses.

905
01:15:17,180 --> 01:15:19,180
The structure does not support

906
01:15:19,180 --> 01:15:22,180
ratio level interpretation.

907
01:15:22,180 --> 01:15:24,529
So the problem here is

908
01:15:24,529 --> 01:15:28,529
mixing incompatible scale types.

909
01:15:28,529 --> 01:15:31,529
The mathematical looks correct,

910
01:15:31,529 --> 01:15:33,529
but the measurement theory

911
01:15:33,529 --> 01:15:38,119
is violated.

912
01:15:38,119 --> 01:15:40,119
This example teaches us

913
01:15:40,119 --> 01:15:45,270
something critical.

914
01:15:45,270 --> 01:15:48,270
When designing software matrix,

915
01:15:48,270 --> 01:15:52,270
we must not only check the formula,

916
01:15:52,270 --> 01:15:56,289
we must check the scale types

917
01:15:56,289 --> 01:15:58,289
of every component.

918
01:15:58,289 --> 01:16:02,979
Otherwise we may

919
01:16:02,979 --> 01:16:04,979
produce numbers

920
01:16:04,979 --> 01:16:06,979
that look scientific but

921
01:16:06,979 --> 01:16:10,140
are theoretically meaningless.

922
01:16:10,140 --> 01:16:14,140
They will not have any meaning.

923
01:16:14,140 --> 01:16:17,619
So here the key lesson is

924
01:16:17,619 --> 01:16:19,619
combining numbers

925
01:16:19,619 --> 01:16:23,060
is easy.

926
01:16:23,060 --> 01:16:27,060
Combining scales correctly

927
01:16:27,060 --> 01:16:40,880
is much harder.

928
01:16:40,880 --> 01:16:41,880
The poison pill

929
01:16:41,880 --> 01:16:45,000
in dimensional analysis.

930
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:46,000
Now let's examine

931
01:16:46,000 --> 01:16:48,000
what we can call

932
01:16:48,000 --> 01:16:50,000
the poison pill

933
01:16:50,000 --> 01:16:53,000
in dimensional analysis.

934
01:16:53,000 --> 01:16:55,869
Now consider

935
01:16:55,869 --> 01:17:00,640
this effort model.

936
01:17:00,640 --> 01:17:02,640
E is equal to

937
01:17:02,640 --> 01:17:08,399
2.7V

938
01:17:08,399 --> 01:17:11,399
plus 121.

939
01:17:11,399 --> 01:17:17,720
W plus 26X plus 12Y

940
01:17:17,720 --> 01:17:25,350
plus 22Z minus 497.

941
01:17:25,350 --> 01:17:27,350
Here we might represent

942
01:17:27,350 --> 01:17:30,960
number of instructions.

943
01:17:30,960 --> 01:17:32,960
X and Y represent

944
01:17:32,960 --> 01:17:35,960
internal and external documents.

945
01:17:35,960 --> 01:17:41,239
Z represents program size.

946
01:17:41,239 --> 01:17:46,510
And W is subjective complex

947
01:17:46,510 --> 01:17:48,510
rating.

948
01:17:48,510 --> 01:17:51,859
At first glance,

949
01:17:51,859 --> 01:17:54,859
this equation looks detailed

950
01:17:54,859 --> 01:17:56,859
and sophisticated.

951
01:17:56,859 --> 01:18:00,859
Many variables, weighted coefficients,

952
01:18:00,859 --> 01:18:03,859
even a constant term.

953
01:18:03,859 --> 01:18:05,859
It feels scientific.

954
01:18:05,859 --> 01:18:09,119
But there is a hidden problem.

955
01:18:09,119 --> 01:18:11,119
The variable W is only

956
01:18:11,119 --> 01:18:15,119
an ordinal scale measure.

957
01:18:15,119 --> 01:18:17,529
It represents a ranking

958
01:18:17,529 --> 01:18:19,529
or subjective rating

959
01:18:19,529 --> 01:18:21,529
of complexity.

960
01:18:21,529 --> 01:18:23,979
It does not have

961
01:18:23,979 --> 01:18:25,979
equal intervals

962
01:18:25,979 --> 01:18:26,979
and it does not have

963
01:18:26,979 --> 01:18:28,979
a true zero.

964
01:18:28,979 --> 01:18:32,880
This is the poison pill.

965
01:18:32,880 --> 01:18:35,880
Because omega is ordinal,

966
01:18:35,880 --> 01:18:37,880
the entire result E

967
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:41,260
collapses to ordinal scale.

968
01:18:41,260 --> 01:18:44,260
According to the weakest link rule,

969
01:18:44,260 --> 01:18:46,260
a derivative measure

970
01:18:46,260 --> 01:18:48,289
cannot be stronger

971
01:18:48,289 --> 01:18:51,289
than its weakest components.

972
01:18:51,289 --> 01:18:56,079
It does not matter

973
01:18:56,079 --> 01:19:00,079
what Y, X, Y and Z

974
01:19:00,079 --> 01:19:03,079
might be ratio scale.

975
01:19:03,079 --> 01:19:07,079
The presence of one ordinal input forces

976
01:19:07,079 --> 01:19:09,079
the final measure

977
01:19:09,079 --> 01:19:11,079
down to ordinal.

978
01:19:11,079 --> 01:19:22,279
Yet the authors claim that

979
01:19:22,279 --> 01:19:24,279
it represents effort

980
01:19:24,279 --> 01:19:26,279
in personal months.

981
01:19:26,279 --> 01:19:30,369
Which is a ratio scale quantity

982
01:19:30,369 --> 01:19:33,529
that claim cannot be justified.

983
01:19:33,529 --> 01:19:39,189
At best, this formula provides

984
01:19:39,189 --> 01:19:41,189
a ranking of efforts.

985
01:19:41,189 --> 01:19:43,409
It might tell us that

986
01:19:43,409 --> 01:19:46,409
one project is likely to require

987
01:19:46,409 --> 01:19:49,409
more effort than another.

988
01:19:49,409 --> 01:19:52,409
But it cannot meaningfully tell us

989
01:19:52,409 --> 01:19:55,409
that the project requires

990
01:19:55,409 --> 01:19:57,409
twice as many persons

991
01:19:57,409 --> 01:19:59,409
months as another.

992
01:19:59,409 --> 01:20:15,430
So this example teaches

993
01:20:15,430 --> 01:20:17,430
a very practical lesson.

994
01:20:17,430 --> 01:20:20,619
Even one improperly scaled variable

995
01:20:20,619 --> 01:20:23,619
can invalidate the scale type

996
01:20:23,619 --> 01:20:26,619
of an entire model.

997
01:20:26,619 --> 01:20:31,359
Before trusting any complex equation,

998
01:20:31,359 --> 01:20:33,359
we must carefully examine

999
01:20:33,359 --> 01:20:36,359
every input variable.

1000
01:20:36,359 --> 01:20:39,579
One subjective ordinal component

1001
01:20:39,579 --> 01:20:42,579
can quietly destroy

1002
01:20:42,579 --> 01:20:44,579
ratio level in the model.

1003
01:20:44,579 --> 01:20:48,159
And that is why

1004
01:20:48,159 --> 01:20:51,159
dimensional analysis in measurement theory

1005
01:20:51,159 --> 01:20:54,159
is not just mathematics.

1006
01:20:54,159 --> 01:21:00,159
It is protection against false precision.

1007
01:21:00,159 --> 01:21:17,619
Now let's bring everything together

1008
01:21:17,619 --> 01:21:19,619
with a checklist for

1009
01:21:19,619 --> 01:21:22,680
Regius measurements.

1010
01:21:22,680 --> 01:21:24,909
If we want to avoid

1011
01:21:24,909 --> 01:21:27,909
the fallacy of a single number

1012
01:21:27,909 --> 01:21:29,909
the trap of

1013
01:21:29,909 --> 01:21:31,909
a single number

1014
01:21:31,909 --> 01:21:32,909
makes it scales

1015
01:21:32,909 --> 01:21:34,909
and the poison-peel problem

1016
01:21:34,909 --> 01:21:36,909
as we have discussed

1017
01:21:36,909 --> 01:21:38,909
earlier now

1018
01:21:38,909 --> 01:21:41,909
we need a disciplined approach.

1019
01:21:41,909 --> 01:21:46,909
First, identify sub-attributes.

1020
01:21:46,909 --> 01:21:49,260
We should not measure

1021
01:21:49,260 --> 01:21:52,289
quality directly.

1022
01:21:52,289 --> 01:21:54,289
Quality is not just

1023
01:21:54,289 --> 01:21:56,289
primitive attribute.

1024
01:21:56,289 --> 01:22:00,060
Instead, we identify its

1025
01:22:00,060 --> 01:22:04,060
components like reliability,

1026
01:22:04,060 --> 01:22:06,060
like performance,

1027
01:22:06,060 --> 01:22:07,060
like usability,

1028
01:22:07,060 --> 01:22:09,060
like maintainability

1029
01:22:09,060 --> 01:22:12,409
and measure them separately.

1030
01:22:12,409 --> 01:22:18,409
Think in terms of vectors

1031
01:22:18,409 --> 01:22:22,279
but not scalars.

1032
01:22:22,279 --> 01:22:28,279
Second, check for incomparability.

1033
01:22:28,279 --> 01:22:30,310
Ask yourself,

1034
01:22:30,310 --> 01:22:33,310
are you forcing a strict order

1035
01:22:33,310 --> 01:22:35,310
onto something that is

1036
01:22:35,310 --> 01:22:37,310
actually a partial order?

1037
01:22:37,310 --> 01:22:40,880
Just like train versus plane.

1038
01:22:40,880 --> 01:22:44,880
Some entities may be better

1039
01:22:44,880 --> 01:22:46,880
in one dimension

1040
01:22:46,880 --> 01:22:50,199
and worse in another.

1041
01:22:50,199 --> 01:22:53,199
If so, a single ranking

1042
01:22:53,199 --> 01:22:56,720
may distort reality.

1043
01:22:56,720 --> 01:23:03,020
Third, verify scale preservation.

1044
01:23:03,020 --> 01:23:06,439
For every input variable,

1045
01:23:06,439 --> 01:23:10,439
determine its scale type.

1046
01:23:10,439 --> 01:23:12,439
Nominal, ordinal,

1047
01:23:12,439 --> 01:23:14,439
interval ratio

1048
01:23:14,439 --> 01:23:15,439
or absolutes.

1049
01:23:15,439 --> 01:23:17,439
This is not optional.

1050
01:23:17,439 --> 01:23:18,439
It defines what

1051
01:23:18,439 --> 01:23:20,439
mathematical operations

1052
01:23:20,439 --> 01:23:22,439
are meaningful.

1053
01:23:22,439 --> 01:23:25,460
Fourth, apply the weakest

1054
01:23:25,460 --> 01:23:27,460
link test.

1055
01:23:27,460 --> 01:23:30,779
After combining measures,

1056
01:23:30,779 --> 01:23:33,779
check the weakest input scale.

1057
01:23:33,779 --> 01:23:35,909
The result cannot be

1058
01:23:35,909 --> 01:23:37,909
stronger than that.

1059
01:23:37,909 --> 01:23:42,039
If one component is ordinal,

1060
01:23:42,039 --> 01:23:44,039
the final measure cannot

1061
01:23:44,039 --> 01:23:46,039
legitimately claim

1062
01:23:46,039 --> 01:23:48,039
ratio level meaning.

1063
01:23:48,039 --> 01:23:53,880
Finally, perform

1064
01:23:53,880 --> 01:23:56,880
wide sense validation.

1065
01:23:56,880 --> 01:23:59,390
Does this formula behave

1066
01:23:59,390 --> 01:24:03,029
correctly under rescaling?

1067
01:24:03,029 --> 01:24:05,029
If you change units,

1068
01:24:05,029 --> 01:24:07,250
for example,

1069
01:24:07,250 --> 01:24:08,250
from lines

1070
01:24:08,250 --> 01:24:10,800
to codes

1071
01:24:10,800 --> 01:24:14,079
to thousands of lines,

1072
01:24:14,079 --> 01:24:15,079
does the structure

1073
01:24:15,079 --> 01:24:17,560
remain valid?

1074
01:24:17,560 --> 01:24:19,560
A meaningful model must

1075
01:24:19,560 --> 01:24:21,560
survive unit transformations

1076
01:24:21,560 --> 01:24:24,560
without breaking its logic.

1077
01:24:24,560 --> 01:24:28,170
This checklist

1078
01:24:28,170 --> 01:24:32,359
is not just theoretical.

1079
01:24:32,359 --> 01:24:36,130
It is a practical filter.

1080
01:24:36,130 --> 01:24:40,289
Before accepting any software metric,

1081
01:24:40,289 --> 01:24:43,289
we can apply these five steps

1082
01:24:43,289 --> 01:24:45,289
and immediately detect

1083
01:24:45,289 --> 01:24:48,289
many common errors.

1084
01:24:48,289 --> 01:24:52,539
So instead of asking,

1085
01:24:52,539 --> 01:24:59,989
so instead of asking,

1086
01:24:59,989 --> 01:25:04,079
does this metric look reasonable?

1087
01:25:04,079 --> 01:25:06,079
A better question is,

1088
01:25:06,079 --> 01:25:08,079
does this metric respect

1089
01:25:08,079 --> 01:25:13,649
the rules of measurement theory?

1090
01:25:13,649 --> 01:25:15,649
Now we have the last slide.

1091
01:25:15,649 --> 01:25:17,649
What we have?

1092
01:25:17,649 --> 01:25:19,649
Nine minutes

1093
01:25:19,649 --> 01:25:24,970
to finish this week's course.

1094
01:25:24,970 --> 01:25:33,720
Yes.

1095
01:25:33,720 --> 01:25:39,060
Measurement is relationship preservation.

1096
01:25:39,060 --> 01:25:42,399
Now we arrive

1097
01:25:42,399 --> 01:25:44,399
at the central principle.

1098
01:25:44,399 --> 01:25:49,039
Measurement is relationship preservation.

1099
01:25:49,039 --> 01:25:53,479
Everything we discussed,

1100
01:25:53,479 --> 01:25:56,899
partial orders,

1101
01:25:56,899 --> 01:25:59,670
vector representation,

1102
01:25:59,670 --> 01:26:01,670
derivatives,

1103
01:26:01,670 --> 01:26:03,670
measurements,

1104
01:26:03,670 --> 01:26:08,760
weakest link rule

1105
01:26:08,760 --> 01:26:14,000
leads to one core idea,

1106
01:26:14,000 --> 01:26:20,109
the representation condition.

1107
01:26:20,109 --> 01:26:23,109
To measure something

1108
01:26:23,109 --> 01:26:26,109
means to define a mapping

1109
01:26:26,109 --> 01:26:29,109
from real-world entities

1110
01:26:29,109 --> 01:26:32,199
into a number system

1111
01:26:32,199 --> 01:26:34,199
in such a way that

1112
01:26:34,199 --> 01:26:36,199
we absorb relationships

1113
01:26:36,199 --> 01:26:41,859
and relationships are preserved.

1114
01:26:41,859 --> 01:26:44,859
That is the essence of measurement.

1115
01:26:44,859 --> 01:26:48,529
If in the real world

1116
01:26:48,529 --> 01:26:52,979
system A is better than system B

1117
01:26:52,979 --> 01:26:56,489
in a clearly defined way,

1118
01:26:56,489 --> 01:27:00,489
then our numerical representation

1119
01:27:00,489 --> 01:27:04,510
must reflect that.

1120
01:27:04,510 --> 01:27:09,699
If two systems are incomparable in reality,

1121
01:27:09,699 --> 01:27:11,699
our measurements must

1122
01:27:11,699 --> 01:27:16,699
not force an artificial ranking.

1123
01:27:16,699 --> 01:27:20,399
Measurement is not about

1124
01:27:20,399 --> 01:27:22,399
producing numbers.

1125
01:27:22,399 --> 01:27:25,399
It's about preserving structure.

1126
01:27:25,399 --> 01:27:28,899
When we assign numbers

1127
01:27:28,899 --> 01:27:31,899
but destroy the relationship

1128
01:27:31,899 --> 01:27:34,899
between entities,

1129
01:27:34,899 --> 01:27:38,060
we are not measuring.

1130
01:27:38,060 --> 01:27:41,159
We are generating noise.

1131
01:27:41,159 --> 01:27:45,079
That's why intuitive understanding

1132
01:27:45,079 --> 01:27:51,239
must precise measurements.

1133
01:27:51,239 --> 01:27:55,199
Before creating a metric,

1134
01:27:55,199 --> 01:27:58,199
we must clearly understand

1135
01:27:58,199 --> 01:28:02,810
the attributes we want to measure.

1136
01:28:02,810 --> 01:28:06,840
What are its components?

1137
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:11,840
What relationships exist between entities?

1138
01:28:11,840 --> 01:28:15,130
Is the order strict or partial?

1139
01:28:15,130 --> 01:28:17,130
Are there trade-offs?

1140
01:28:17,130 --> 01:28:21,350
If we skip this step

1141
01:28:21,350 --> 01:28:25,350
and jump directly to formulas,

1142
01:28:25,350 --> 01:28:27,350
we risk building

1143
01:28:27,350 --> 01:28:31,350
an elegant but meaningless matrix.

1144
01:28:31,350 --> 01:28:36,470
So the final takeaway is this.

1145
01:28:36,470 --> 01:28:39,470
Measurement is not arithmetic.

1146
01:28:39,470 --> 01:28:45,600
Measurement is structure preservation.

1147
01:28:45,600 --> 01:28:48,359
Anything less,

1148
01:28:48,359 --> 01:28:51,750
is just noise.

